SURVO84ED 81 300    81 S20                                                       *SAVE EDQ0S1                                                                     *LOAD EDQ                                                                        *                                                                                *PLAY?                                                                           *PLAY is a Survo operation for creating of sound files (WAV)                     *and for playback of them                                                        *                                                                                *  1 = PLAY SOUND(S) for playback of WAV files                                   *  2 = PLAY DATA     for creating sound files from Survo data                    *  3 = Sound signals in tutorials                                               C*  4 = Sound signals for mouse clicks and activations                           C*                                                                                %1=PLAY_S 2=PLAY_D 3=TUTSOUND? 4=ACTSOUND                                        *@SELECT                                                                         *                                                                                *                                                                                *PLAY_S?                                                                         *PLAY SOUND <pathname of a sound file>                                           *plays back synchronously a given sound file.                                    *PLAY SOUND <sound file>,<max.time>                                              *plays back asynchronously a given sound file using max.time (in millisec.)      *PLAY SOUNDS                                                                     *sound_file_1                                                                    *sound_file_2                                                                    *...                                                                             *plays back synchronously a series of sound files.                               *Default directory of Survo sound files is <Survo>\U\SND .                       *Default type of a sound file is .WAV. In playback Survo is using                *the WIN32 API function PlaySound().                                             *Ready-made sound files (.WAV) in your PC can be found, for example, by          *WHERE C:\*.WAV                                                                  *Examples:                                                                       *PLAY SOUND Fringilla.coelebs                                                    *PLAY SOUNDS                                                                     *Cuculus.canorus                                                                 *Cuculus.canorus                                                                 *Fringilla.coelebs                                                               *                                                                                *@END                                                                            *                                                                                *PLAY_D?                                                                         *Creating sound files from Survo data                                            *                                                                                *There are two alternatives for making sounds based on Survo data.               *                                                                                *1. Sounds from raw data:                                                        *Consecutive values of one (mono) or two (stereo) variables in a Survo           *sound files can be saved as such in a WAV file by PLAY DATA command             *and played back by PLAY SOUND commmand.                                         *                                                                                *2. Mapping data values to given sounds:                                         *Consecutive values of selected variables in Survo data files can be             *replaced by sounds and "played" by                                              *PLAY DATA <data> / VOICES=<list of given voices>.                               *                                                                                *Description of these alternatives not yet ready!                                *Examples (in Finnish) by                                                        */LOAD <Survo>\U\SND\PLAYDATA                                                    *                                                                                *@END                                                                            *                                                                                *ACTSOUND?                                                                       *When making Flash demos, activations and mouse clicks can be                    *recorded by inserting a line                                                    *                                                                                *act_sounds=SUR_ACT,SUR_ML,SUR_MR                                                *                                                                                *in the SURVO.APU file. The default WAV files listed above are                   *in the directory <Survo>\U\SND.                                                 *After making this modification and restarting Survo, the sounds                 *are activated by keystrokes F2 L E and deactivated by F2 L e.                   *When the sounds are activated,                                                  *the first sound will heard when a command is activated by ESC or                *a double-click.                                                                 *The second sound relates to the mouse click by the leftmost button.             *The third sound relates to the mouse click by the rightmost button.             *@END                                                                            *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *  1 = Sound files from raw data                                                 *  2 = Mapping data values to given sounds                                       *                                                                                %1=PLAY_D1 2=PLAY_D2?                                                            *                                                                                *PLAY_D1?                                                                        *Sound files from raw data                                                       *                                                                                *PLAY DATA <Survo_data>,<variable>                                               *moves the values of <variable> in <Survo_data> in a sound file                  *given by a WAV specification.                                                   *The default format of the WAV file is 16 bit mono with 11025 Hz                 *sample rate.                                                                    *Values of <variable> must be in the interval [-32767,32767].                    *                                                                                *Example 1:                                                                      *s(X):=sin(X*ORDER)                                                              *FILE MAKE DAT,1,24000,X,2                                                       *VAR X=8000*(s(0.2)+s(0.25)+s(0.3)) TO DAT / Pure major triad                    *PLAY DATA DAT,X  / WAV=MAJOR  Making file MAJOR.WAV from X in DAT               *PLAY SOUND MAJOR / Playback of MAJOR                                            *VAR X=8000*(s(0.2)+s(0.2*6/5)+s(0.3)) TO DAT / Pure minor triad                 *PLAY DATA DAT,X  / WAV=MINOR                                                    *PLAY SOUND MINOR / Playback of MINOR                                            *@END                                                                            *................................................................................*Example 2:                                                                      *s(X):=sin(X*ORDER)                                                              *FILE MAKE DAT,1,36000,X,2                                                       *VAR X=8000*(s(0.2)+s(0.2*k)+s(0.3)) TO DAT                                      *k=if(ORDER<4001)then(6/5)else(k2)                                               *k2=if(ORDER>28000)then(5/4)else(k3)                                             *k3=6/5+(5/4-6/5)/23999*(ORDER-4000)                                             *PLAY DATA DAT,X / WAV=MM                                                        *PLAY SOUND MM                                                                   *FILE SHOW DAT                                                                   *................................................................................*                                                                                *                                                                                *GPLOT DAT,TIME,k                                                                *LINE=1                                                                          *@END                                                                            *                                                                                *PLAY_D2?                                                                        *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *@END                                                                            *                                                                                *STAT DAT,CUR+1                                                                  *Basic statistics: DAT N=36000                                                   *Variable: X        ~k                                                           *Constant= 1                                                                     *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *                                                                                *           